title: Arsenal ´didn´t find enough consistency´ in Palace draw, rues Arteta
description: Mikel Arteta conceded Arsenal “didn’t find enough consistency” against Crystal Palace as the Gunners were held to a 2-2 draw. Arteta’s side were twice pegged back at the Emirates Stadium, failing to win a Premier League game when leading on two occasions for only the third time under Arteta. title: Getafe 0-1 Real Madrid: Guler stunner keeps flickering title hopes alive
description: Arda Guler’s superb first-half strike earned Real Madrid a nervy 1-0 win at Getafe on Wednesday, moving back to within four points of LaLiga leaders Barcelona. Hansi Flick’s Blaugrana had recorded their own 1-0 win against Mallorca 24 hours earlier, meaning Carlo Ancelotti’s men needed these three precious points to keep their title hopes alive.
